1
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:41,080
Today we are going to the studio

2
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:42,799
to film the final episode.

3
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,799
Looks pretty good.

4
00:00:53,799 --> 00:00:54,759
Looks pretty good.

5
00:01:02,599 --> 00:01:03,959
Let's see if we can eat this.

6
00:01:05,599 --> 00:01:06,559
Is it too spicy?

7
00:01:11,319 --> 00:01:12,360
Machine gun fire

8
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:14,199
You aim, and I'll hit wherever you point

9
00:01:14,919 --> 00:01:16,839
Are you nervous seeing your idol?

10
00:01:16,839 --> 00:01:17,639
I'm so nervous

11
00:01:18,639 --> 00:01:19,639
I really like Jing Tian

12
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:25,480
Done

13
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,480
I might forget in a while

14
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,400
I might too

15
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,599
The people I loved

16
00:01:33,599 --> 00:01:36,599
None of them stayed by my side

17
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,959
I am "Christmas Knot"

18
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:44,879
So nervous

19
00:01:48,639 --> 00:01:50,400
During the first episode, Tiantian asked me

20
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:50,800
right?

21
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:53,480
what the final winner's surprise would be.

22
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:55,160
Alright, next on our show, we keep our promises.

23
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:56,199
It's time to deliver.

24
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:57,000
There really is one.

25
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,959
Yes, let's present the surprise.

26
00:02:00,839 --> 00:02:01,680
What is it?

27
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,160
As long as it's not a scare.

28
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:04,879
What?

29
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:05,800
Wang Nengneng is coming over.

30
00:02:06,839 --> 00:02:07,839
Wang Nengneng is here.

31
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,880
Really

32
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,639
Encore

33
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:24,960
Why do you look like you've seen a ghost?

34
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,800
Great!

35
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:36,520
Is it real? Is it a real person?

36
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,199
No.

37
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:39,399
Why do I feel like I've seen a "ghost"?

38
00:02:39,399 --> 00:02:40,520
So scared.

39
00:02:44,639 --> 00:02:45,919
Hello

40
00:02:45,919 --> 00:02:46,639
Luo Ying

41
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,960
Hello

42
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,119
Scissors hand

43
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,240
Scared me to death

44
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,119
Calm down

45
00:02:53,119 --> 00:02:54,000
You calm down

46
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,039
What's wrong with you

47
00:02:56,039 --> 00:02:57,199
Scared to death

48
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,600
We are the flag bearers, you should know

49
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:03,919
Neng Neng, you are amazing, Neng Neng

50
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:13,199
No, keep it low-key, I have a family.

51
00:03:15,639 --> 00:03:16,679
What happened?

52
00:03:18,119 --> 00:03:19,839
Can I come earlier next time?

53
00:03:20,759 --> 00:03:22,919
It ended before I could understand it.

54
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:26,479
Really.

55
00:03:26,479 --> 00:03:26,960
Yes.

56
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,320
Guo Qilin

57
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,080
A family

58
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,960
She really likes Guo Qilin.

59
00:03:34,559 --> 00:03:35,479
We all know.

60
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:39,080
She just got Guo Qilin's autograph a few days ago.

61
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,080
She was very happy.

62
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,240
Really?

63
00:03:41,679 --> 00:03:42,559
A family, a family.

64
00:03:43,639 --> 00:03:45,479
The game results you told me about were just us playing.

65
00:03:45,479 --> 00:03:47,759
Are you married?

66
00:03:47,759 --> 00:03:48,479
So soon?

67
00:03:48,479 --> 00:03:49,360
You went to Chengdu.

68
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,119
Wait a moment, control your emotions.

69
00:03:51,119 --> 00:03:51,800
Wait a moment.

70
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:56,039
It was really surprising.

71
00:03:58,559 --> 00:04:00,479
We all felt a bit shy like this.

72
00:04:00,479 --> 00:04:01,279
Yes, shy.

73
00:04:01,279 --> 00:04:02,559
We should have been nervous.

74
00:04:02,559 --> 00:04:03,800
We should have felt surprised.

75
00:04:05,279 --> 00:04:06,559
We thought it was over.

76
00:04:06,559 --> 00:04:08,080
We are coming in soon.

77
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:10,360
But we found out you were more nervous than us.

78
00:04:10,839 --> 00:04:12,039
We were excited.

79
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:51,760
Hello

80
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:52,839
Baby

81
00:04:52,839 --> 00:04:53,559
Hello

82
00:04:54,679 --> 00:04:55,079
Am I pretty?

83
00:04:55,079 --> 00:04:56,079
You are so beautiful

84
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,760
Let's go

85
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,279
Happy birthday, Lao Luo

86
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:06,640
Happy birthday

87
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,160
Happy birthday

88
00:05:09,519 --> 00:05:11,079
You are very scattered

89
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,239
Shun Shun

90
00:05:22,559 --> 00:05:23,399
Happy birthday

91
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:25,519
Thank you, Shun Shun

92
00:05:25,519 --> 00:05:27,200
Happy birthday

93
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,279
Here, a birthday gift

94
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:29,600
Thank you

95
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,320
May you have a child soon

96
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,480
What kind of gift is this

97
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,239
Why wish for a child soon

98
00:05:35,239 --> 00:05:36,279
He asked me to come over

99
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,679
Yes, my friends just now too

100
00:05:38,679 --> 00:05:39,959
Wang Neng Neng asked them to come over

101
00:05:42,079 --> 00:05:44,279
Here, this song is dedicated to my lover

102
00:05:44,279 --> 00:05:49,040
I am like a fish in your lotus pond

103
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:53,040
Just to stay with you under the bright moonlight

104
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,000
Stop laughing

105
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:58,679
Swimming through the seasons, the lotus flowers still fragrant

106
00:05:58,679 --> 00:06:02,119
Waiting for you in the middle of the water

107
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,760
Not bad

108
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:09,480
Singing your song on the rooftop

109
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:12,040
On the rooftop with the one I love

110
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:17,920
Let the stars adorn the most romantic night

111
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:20,679
On the rooftop with the one I love

112
00:06:20,679 --> 00:06:26,200
Offer the yellowing night to the loneliest moon

113
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:35,000
Embrace this moment, every second stops

114
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:39,559
Love starts to tangle, dreams are beautiful with you

115
00:06:39,559 --> 00:06:41,000
Sounds good

116
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:45,480
Happy birthday to you

117
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,399
What a big cake

118
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,600
He gave me one

119
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,480
just like the one I gave him before

120
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,839
I wrote a "longevity" character before

121
00:06:54,839 --> 00:06:56,839
then he gave me a longevity peach

122
00:06:56,839 --> 00:06:58,760
Who wrote the "longevity" character for me

123
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,399
I did

124
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,279
Happy birthday, darling

125
00:07:03,279 --> 00:07:05,239
Thank you, darling

126
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,839
Happy birthday

127
00:07:12,839 --> 00:07:14,559
Happy birthday

128
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:16,519
Happy birthday, baby

129
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:17,839
Thank you, baby

130
00:07:20,519 --> 00:07:22,000
The kiss was too short

131
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,399
I can't take it anymore, I'm going to "die"

132
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,839
Thank you for your hard work.

133
00:07:35,839 --> 00:07:36,679
Thanks for your effort.

134
00:07:36,679 --> 00:07:39,239
Thank you for your hard work, Brother Wang.

135
00:07:40,359 --> 00:07:42,839
Later, they laughed so hard they sounded like pigs.

136
00:07:43,799 --> 00:07:44,519
Little pig.

137
00:07:51,399 --> 00:07:52,880
So, what are we going to eat later?

138
00:07:53,959 --> 00:07:55,799
Let's have some grilled chicken.

139
00:07:55,799 --> 00:07:56,559
Alright.

140
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:59,200
Having grilled chicken at night is quite satisfying.

141
00:08:01,119 --> 00:08:02,079
Yes, for the two of you.

142
00:08:08,079 --> 00:08:09,880
It's grilled to medium-rare.

143
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,040
Each of you gets a piece of medium-rare.

144
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:18,359
It's actually been two months since we left the cabin.

145
00:08:18,359 --> 00:08:19,519
I think we still gained something.

146
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:22,000
A lot of great friends.

147
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,359
Big brother is always a legend.

148
00:08:24,799 --> 00:08:26,239
Why are you so...

149
00:08:26,239 --> 00:08:27,359
...admiring of big brother now?

150
00:08:28,359 --> 00:08:30,640
Now you realize your own efforts...

151
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:31,519
...compared to big brother's efforts...

152
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:32,719
...are quite different, right?

153
00:08:34,239 --> 00:08:36,719
Compared to big brother, right?

154
00:08:36,719 --> 00:08:39,000
You're just about the same.

155
00:08:40,719 --> 00:08:42,359
I thought I was flawless.

156
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,760
But it turns out I was full of flaws.

157
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:57,280
I understand you

158
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:15,640
Hello

159
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:17,039
Hello

160
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,159
What is this

161
00:09:19,159 --> 00:09:20,640
Weren't you going to make mulled wine

162
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:21,559
I only brought one bottle

163
00:09:21,559 --> 00:09:22,320
Okay

164
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:23,719
Let's find a place to eat

165
00:09:24,359 --> 00:09:25,080
Okay

166
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:28,039
But we need to buy groceries first, is that okay

167
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:28,719
Okay

168
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,799
Let's buy vegetables first.

169
00:09:34,799 --> 00:09:36,799
I can take two tomatoes.

170
00:09:36,799 --> 00:09:38,640
Is one enough with the chicken?

171
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:39,239
Definitely enough.

172
00:09:39,239 --> 00:09:40,479
Enough.

173
00:09:40,479 --> 00:09:41,479
Thank you.

174
00:09:41,479 --> 00:09:42,520
How much, boss?

175
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,280
Forty yuan.

176
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,239
How much?

177
00:09:44,239 --> 00:09:45,400
Ten yuan and fifty cents.

178
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:46,400
How about ten yuan?

179
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,000
Alright.

180
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,679
I need to buy some seasonings.

181
00:09:51,679 --> 00:09:53,880
This way, the stir-fry won't taste bad.

182
00:09:54,679 --> 00:09:55,760
Seventeen, right?

183
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:56,599
Yes.

184
00:09:56,599 --> 00:09:57,799
I want to eat pickled long beans.

185
00:09:59,679 --> 00:10:01,359
You don't understand what pickled long beans are.

186
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:02,919
I don't know.

187
00:10:04,479 --> 00:10:06,280
Is there anything else you want to eat?

188
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:07,679
I rarely cook.

189
00:10:07,679 --> 00:10:09,320
Nothing else.

190
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,239
Done shopping.

191
00:10:10,239 --> 00:10:11,840
I'll make you some experimental cuisine tonight.

192
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:15,320
We're here.

193
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:18,640
Why did you choose such an artsy place?

194
00:10:19,559 --> 00:10:20,479
It's not your style.

195
00:10:20,479 --> 00:10:22,640
Bringing back memories of the cabin.

196
00:10:24,919 --> 00:10:25,799
Doesn't it look similar?

197
00:10:25,799 --> 00:10:28,559
A bit, it does look like the cabin.

198
00:10:28,559 --> 00:10:30,599
It seems like after we left the cabin,

199
00:10:30,599 --> 00:10:32,880
we haven't cooked together like this.

200
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:35,919
That's why I arranged for us to come here.

201
00:10:35,919 --> 00:10:37,799
We don't have aprons, what do we do?

202
00:10:37,799 --> 00:10:40,039
The main thing is this will get covered in hair.

203
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,400
How about you wear my jacket?

204
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,239
What about you?

205
00:10:45,239 --> 00:10:46,520
I'll just go without.

206
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,440
Aren't you cold?

207
00:10:49,799 --> 00:10:51,000
The sleeves are long.

208
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,440
Wouldn't it be the same if I wore yours?

209
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:54,799
Is that okay?

210
00:10:54,799 --> 00:10:56,119
Can you help me tie my hair?

211
00:11:06,239 --> 00:11:06,960
Is this okay?

212
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:08,719
Do I look good like this?

213
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,640
I need to look good.

214
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:17,919
Okay

215
00:11:18,359 --> 00:11:18,719
Is that okay?

216
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:19,239
Okay

217
00:11:19,239 --> 00:11:19,880
Alright

218
00:11:21,119 --> 00:11:22,640
Move away a bit, I'm so scared

219
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:27,239
Your move was really funny.

220
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:29,719
Horse stance.

221
00:11:32,239 --> 00:11:34,159
I think this will taste really good.

222
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:40,679
Smells good

223
00:11:48,359 --> 00:11:49,080
It's hot

224
00:11:50,119 --> 00:11:51,559
I just burned myself

225
00:11:51,559 --> 00:11:52,679
And you still gave it to me to eat

226
00:11:52,679 --> 00:11:54,239
I was blowing on it for you

227
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,280
It's fine now

228
00:12:06,119 --> 00:12:07,200
It's the taste of Sichuan.

229
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:11,919
I told you I'd make you a Sichuan dish.

230
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:13,719
Isn't it?

231
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,719
Because the fire is too big

232
00:12:20,719 --> 00:12:21,719
We can't let it roll

233
00:12:34,559 --> 00:12:35,559
Let's eat quickly.

234
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:37,640
This is fine.

235
00:12:48,479 --> 00:12:49,239
Eat more.

236
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:51,679
Okay.

237
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:02,320
What are you doing?

238
00:13:03,799 --> 00:13:04,760
Why are you so close?

239
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:05,479
It's cold.

240
00:13:14,119 --> 00:13:15,679
Is there a problem with this?

241
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:18,599
No.

242
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,640
Got sand in my eye again.

243
00:13:31,679 --> 00:13:33,599
Why do you always get stuff in your eyes?

244
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:36,919
I have big eyes too, but I don't have this problem.

245
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:39,280
Maybe my eyelashes are short.

246
00:13:41,159 --> 00:13:42,119
They can't block it.

247
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:48,679
How about I take you back first

248
00:13:48,679 --> 00:13:50,359
and then come back to clean up

249
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:52,000
Alright

250
00:13:58,039 --> 00:13:58,799
Here we are.

251
00:14:05,599 --> 00:14:06,840
I won't go up.

252
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:09,520
Alright.

253
00:14:16,599 --> 00:14:17,599
Go up.

254
00:14:18,559 --> 00:14:19,280
Let's go.

255
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,679
Bye-bye.

256
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,359
Come on, let's get started.

257
00:14:55,359 --> 00:14:56,239
Brother Wang

258
00:14:56,239 --> 00:14:56,919
Okay

259
00:14:58,479 --> 00:14:59,679
Let's record an intro

260
00:15:02,119 --> 00:15:04,000
Today is Brother Wang's cooking day

261
00:15:05,919 --> 00:15:09,159
Yes, I'm responsible for teaching him

262
00:15:09,159 --> 00:15:10,080
Yes

263
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:12,159
I just had a face mask on, I look very messy

264
00:15:12,159 --> 00:15:13,400
But it doesn't matter

265
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,320
He's already used to seeing me like this

266
00:15:16,159 --> 00:15:17,320
And now Brother Wang

267
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:20,159
is going to start cooking tomato beef brisket

268
00:15:23,119 --> 00:15:24,359
Rinse it with water, and then

269
00:15:26,239 --> 00:15:28,239
First, tear off the packaging

270
00:15:28,239 --> 00:15:29,479
Don't worry too much about the camera

271
00:15:29,479 --> 00:15:30,359
Cook first

272
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:36,520
Beef brisket, right?

273
00:15:37,119 --> 00:15:38,479
Yes, be careful with your hand.

274
00:15:38,479 --> 00:15:39,520
I just saw your cut.

275
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,400
I was afraid of cutting my hand.

276
00:15:41,359 --> 00:15:42,880
How could you cut your hand?

277
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,200
I'm such a careful person.

278
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:46,799
Everyone online says chandlerpan

279
00:15:46,799 --> 00:15:47,960
is very careful, okay?

280
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,440
I choose to remain silent.

281
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:55,719
Show off your skills in front of the head chef

282
00:15:55,719 --> 00:15:57,960
Come on, let me put on this cute little bib for you

283
00:16:07,559 --> 00:16:09,080
This bib is so tight on my chest.

284
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:12,599
Look at yourself right now.

285
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:18,000
Why is it so tight when you wear it?

286
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,039
Is this a posture corrector?

287
00:16:26,479 --> 00:16:29,039
Hurry up, cut the beef.

288
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:32,280
Or should we have curry beef brisket?

